======================================================================
SECTION 3: JOINT STACKED MODEL — Direct interaction test
======================================================================

To directly test whether the two error types have DIFFERENT slopes,
we create a stacked/long dataset with one row per observation per error type,
and test the error_type × time interaction.

Stacked dataset: 4800 rows (2 × 2400)
  Perceptual events: 161
  Semantic events:   45

--- G. Stacked: occurred ~ log(Days) × error_type ---
Formula: occurred ~ log_Days * C(etype, Treatment(reference='semantic'))
N observations: 4800
N clusters (UID): 100
Events: 206/4800 (4.29%)

Coefficients:
           Parameter      Coef        SE         z         p        OR     OR_lo     OR_hi
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
           Intercept   -4.4762    0.2802   -15.977    0.0000     0.011     0.007     0.020
C(etype, Treatment(reference='semantic'))[T.perceptual]    1.8324    0.2844     6.443    0.0000     6.249     3.578    10.911
            log_Days    0.6569    0.1777     3.696    0.0002     1.929     1.361     2.733
log_Days:C(etype, Treatment(reference='semantic'))[T.perceptual]   -0.5758    0.1904    -3.024    0.0025     0.562     0.387     0.817

--- H. Stacked: occurred ~ Days × error_type ---
Formula: occurred ~ Days * C(etype, Treatment(reference='semantic'))
N observations: 4800
N clusters (UID): 100
Events: 206/4800 (4.29%)

Coefficients:
